p: \bDid'jer see those folk goin' down to Anastasia's workshop?
\bI don't like what they're up to, not one bit!
\rDid you see those creeps enter town?
\rThey make me nervous. Who knows what they're up to?
\bWhat a weird place to put a workshop.
\bBut no matter! It's time to pay our friend Anastasia a little visit.
\bWhat a weird place to put a workshop.
\bWhat a weird place to put a workshop.
\bWhat a weird place to put a workshop.
\rKepler City's electricity comes from nuclear power.
\rThere's a reactor underground that generates huge amounts of energy every second.
\rIt's actually a lot safer than people give it credit for.\nNuclear power isn't as dangerous as everyone thinks!
\bYou see a lot of Abyssal Cultists around these parts.
\bThere's also a really deep ocean trench just south of here.
\bKepler City is definitely the tech and science city of Torren.
\bEvery innnovation- from Pokeballs to power- all come from here!
\bI absolutely love living here in Kepler.
\bNot only do I love machines, but my parents helped to build it!
\bI want to honor my parents' memories by never moving away!
\bThe leader of the Kepler City Gym is named Anastasia.
\bShe's one heckuva battler- she's a master of both Steel- and Electric-types!
\rI hear there's a Moss Rock over in Murk Forest, to the northeast.
\rIf you're into evolving an Eevee into a Leafeon, that would be the place to do it.
\rAnastasia, our Gym Leader, runs a Machine-themed Gym.
\rShe's almost never there though- she's in the Observatory or working on her own projects in her Lab.
\rI guess that's one of the drawbacks to being a Gym Leader with an actual job!
\bMy wife and I have been saving our money to afford a nice home.
\bHopefully, we'll be able to move in together to live a nice quiet life.\nAck, if only homes weren't so expensive here.
\bWhile the internet is great, the costs are through the roof!
\bMaybe we'll move to Hekate Town instead.
\bI was out in the tall grass, and I came across two Pokemon at once!
\bI was only able to catch one of them though. What a shame!
\bI'm afraid I can't let you in- access is restricted!
